        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 5:44PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Uptown Charlotte, or near Mt Holly, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntersville, Northeast Charlotte, Northwest Charlotte, Mt Holly,
Belmont, Lowell, Westport, Mcadenville, Charlotte Douglas Airport,
and Paw Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
